ation. In contrast, in the presence of\nhydrophilic plates, water structure is insensitive to P. Hence, our results\nsuggest that upon pressurization, hydrophobic plates behave as `soft' surfaces\n(in the sense of accommodating pressure-dependent changes in water structure)\nwhile hydrophilic walls behave as `hard' surfaces.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 2 Mar 2006 00:42:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-08"}
